White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki welcomed back Michael Regan, the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), to discuss the bipartisan Infrastructure Framework. The framework includes investments in clean water infrastructure, such as replacing lead water pipes and modernizing wastewater systems. Regan also discussed the President's meeting on wildfire preparedness and the EPA's efforts to provide reliable information on air quality during wildfires. He emphasized the need to rebuild infrastructure that can withstand climate impacts and highlighted the importance of clean and healthy drinking water for all communities. Regan also mentioned the President's commitment to water infrastructure and climate resilience, as well as the creation of jobs in the water industry. Psaki also addressed questions about water quality, wildfires, and other topics including protests, police reform, international travel, and COVID-19 vaccinations.